Supplementary 1. Description of the data

A. Distribution of ES

df_main$outlier_pre_post = ifelse(
  is_outlier(df_main$yi - df_main$yi_p), df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_main$outlier = ifelse(is_outlier(df_main$yi), 
                         df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_plot = df_main %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(yi, yi_p), names_to = "es_type", values_to = "smd") 
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi"] <- "Pre-post SMD"
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi_p"] <- "Post SMD"
df_plot$ID = rep(1:(nrow(df_plot)/2), each = 2)
ggplot(df_plot, aes(x = outcome, y = smd)) +

Supplementary 2. Main analysis

A. Results

V.SCE  <- impute_covariance_matrix(vi = df_main$vi, 
                                   cluster = df_main$study_ID, 
                                   r = 0.8,
                                   return_list = FALSE,
                                   smooth_vi = TRUE,
                                   subgroup = df_main$outcome)

metafor.SCE <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                               mods =  ~ outcome - 1,
                               data = df_main,
                               random = ~ outcome | study_ID,
                               struct = "DIAG",
                               sparse = TRUE)

res.main = coef_sand(model = metafor.SCE, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.main$outcome = gsub("outcome", "", res.main$outcome)
res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)] = round(res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)], 3)
res.main$Analysis = "Primary analysis"

kbl(res.main) %>%
  kable_classic()
outcome beta SE tstat df p_Satt CI_L CI_U Analysis
interoception 0.253 0.085 2.975 8.231 0.017 0.058 0.448 Primary analysis
symptoms 0.323 0.091 3.563 8.315 0.007 0.116 0.531 Primary analysis

Heterogeneity

metafor.SCE
## 
## Multivariate Meta-Analysis Model (k = 46; method: REML)
## 
## Variance Components:
## 
## outer factor: study_ID (nlvls = 12)
## inner factor: outcome  (nlvls = 2)
## 
##             estim    sqrt  k.lvl  fixed          level 
## tau^2.1    0.0424  0.2060     33     no  interoception 
## tau^2.2    0.0497  0.2229     13     no       symptoms 
## 
## Test for Residual Heterogeneity:
## QE(df = 44) = 221.4067, p-val < .0001
## 
## Test of Moderators (coefficients 1:2):
## QM(df = 2) = 21.6871, p-val < .0001
## 
## Model Results:
## 
##                       estimate      se    zval    pval   ci.lb   ci.ub      
## outcomeinteroception    0.2527  0.0845  2.9925  0.0028  0.0872  0.4182   ** 
## outcomesymptoms         0.3234  0.0906  3.5682  0.0004  0.1458  0.5011  *** 
## 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
W <- solve(V.SCE)
X <- model.matrix(metafor.SCE)
P <- W - W %*% X %*% solve(t(X) %*% W %*% X) %*% t(X) %*% W
c(100 * metafor.SCE$tau2[1] / (metafor.SCE$tau2[1] + (sum(df_main$outcome == "interoception")-1)/sum(diag(P)[df_main$outcome == "interoception"])),
  100 * metafor.SCE$tau2[2] / (metafor.SCE$tau2[2] + (sum(df_main$outcome == "symptoms")-1)/sum(diag(P)[df_main$outcome == "symptoms"])))
## [1] 83.87086 77.52895

D. Small-study effects

Square root of the eff. sample size

sse.1 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,

names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "study_ID"] = "author"
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "outcome"] = "factor"

I. Jackknife meta-analysis

res.JK = NULL
for (study in unique(df_main$study_ID)) {
  res.JK_transit = NA
  dat_minus_one = NA
  dat_minus_one = subset(df_main, study_ID != study)
  V.SCE  <- impute_covariance_matrix(vi = dat_minus_one$vi, 
                                   cluster = dat_minus_one$study_ID, 
                                   r = 0.8,
                                   return_list = FALSE,
                                   smooth_vi = TRUE,
                                   subgroup = dat_minus_one$outcome)

  metafor.SCE <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                               mods =  ~ outcome - 1,
                               data = dat_minus_one,
                               random = ~ outcome | study_ID,
                               struct = "DIAG",
                               sparse = TRUE)

  res.JK_transit = coef_sand(model = metafor.SCE, vcov = "CR2", 
                     cluster = dat_minus_one$study_ID)
  res.JK_transit[,2:ncol(res.JK_transit)] = round(res.JK_transit[,2:ncol(res.JK_transit)], 3)
  res.JK_transit$outcome = gsub("outcome", "", res.JK_transit$outcome)
  res.JK_transit$excluded_study = study
  res.JK = rbind(res.JK, res.JK_transit)
}

J. Varying interoception scales

dat_S10 = df_main %>%
  filter(outcome == "interoception")
dat_S10$scale = with(dat_S10, 
    ifelse(grepl("_MAIA_", ID_out, fixed=TRUE), "MAIA",
    ifelse(grepl("_SBC_", ID_out, fixed=TRUE), "SBC",
    ifelse(grepl("_FFMQ_", ID_out, fixed=TRUE), "FFMQ", NA))))

V.SCE10  <- impute_covariance_matrix(vi = dat_S10$vi, 
                                   cluster = dat_S10$study_ID, 
                                   r = 0.8,
                                   return_list = FALSE,
                                   smooth_vi = TRUE,
                                   subgroup = dat_S10$scale)

metafor.SCE10 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE10,
                               mods =  ~ scale,
                               data = dat_S10,
                               random = ~ scale | study_ID,
                               struct = "DIAG",

robust.rma.mv(metafor.SCE10, cluster=dat_S10$study_ID)
